      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S, finished in Arctic Silver Metallic. This 996.2 flagship features the naturally aspirated 3.6L flat-six engine producing 315 hp and 273 lb-ft of torque, mated to a precise 6-speed manual transaxle. The drivetrain is anchored by a permanent all-wheel-drive system and the coveted wide-body chassis derived from the 911 Turbo. Mechanical highlights include a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit, recent borescope inspection showing zero cylinder wall scoring, and a factory-spec Turbo-derived braking system with four-piston monobloc calipers and cross-drilled rotors. The suspension geometry remains taut with no bushing deflection, and the VarioCam Plus timing system operates with surgical precision. This is a concours-level example with zero cosmetic or mechanical flaws, offering the visceral, analog engagement of the last cable-throttle 911 generation.",
